Ana de Armas, 34, made a show-stopping appearance at the 80th Golden Globe Awards on Tuesday. The Cuban-born star posed for the cameras wearing a custom Louis Vuitton dress that featured a geometrical pattern created by silver studs. She paired the black, strapless dress with black heeled sandals and a sparkling bracelet. The actress kept her makeup look classic with a bold cat eye and a berry lip, which she paired with a peachy blush. She wore her long, luscious tresses down in a middle parting that framed her features. Ana was nominated for Best Performance by an Actress in a Motion Picture, Drama for her work in Blonde, the “fictionalisation” of Marilyn Monroe's life.